    "title": "Utilizing Enhanced Deep Contextualized Word Embeddings for Downstream Tasks",
    "abstract": "The Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers, more commonly known as BERT, is a Language model which uses transformers to produce contextualized word embeddings. Deep bidirectional models have been shown to encode meanings in the hidden layers of BERT, which gave rise to ELMo: word representations which incorporate the hidden states of a neural network. We aim to improve on this paradigm by allowing a larger variability in these deep contextualized word embeddings for higher semantic understanding and learnability. We take inspiration from ELMo, producing a new form of contextualized embeddings which are given by trainable parameters.",
    "venue": "",
